          <title>Big Ten fines Michigan and Ohio State $100,000 each for postgame melee</title>
          <description><![CDATA[ROSEMONT, Ill. (AP) — The Big Ten Conference announced it fined Michigan and Ohio State $100,000 each for violating the conference's sportsmanship policy for the on-field melee at the end of the Wolverines' win in Columbus on Saturday.]]></description>
